Cool + late spring hit 80 degrees for first time yesterday.

0.3" rain since last report (8/12/96).  High temps. In low to mid 80's.
1.0" rain since last report. high temps. generally in low to mid 80's.

Maximum temperature are 10 degrees below normal over last 10 days.
Very dry spring. pine pollen on lake.
1.2" rain 5/30.  Max. temps. low 60's last week.
1.4" rain yesterday.  Early June was cool 10 degrees below normal.
2+ inches rain in past week.  Temps in upper 80's.
Hot and humid high temp. in the 90's.
Windy day.  1 inch of rain in past week.
5.25 inches of rain in the past 4 days.  Prior to that lake was very low.  Outlet creek had been dry for 2 weeks.
0.5 inches of rain one week ago.

Have had 4 days below normal temps.
1.7" rain 2 days ago. temp  80 F today.
6" of rain since last reading.  Weather hot + very humid.
Very hot- temps in 90s until 3 days ago. normal now.
2.1" rain 2 days ago. temps in low 70s.

Some night temps close to 50 F.
Saw a loon on the lake several days ago.
Hundreds of sea gulls making a nuisance of themselves on lake.
Sept was a very dry month.  Little over 2 inches total.
Last rain 2 weeks ago.  Had 6 days with max. temps. in the 80's.
Cooler than normal weather past week. near freezing last 2 nights.
Weather has been rainy and mostly cloudy since last reading.
Weather has been cool- cloudy and rainy since last reading.
Bright- sunny day but windy. no whitecaps.
Loons on lake yesterday- a rare sight.
Not available for fly over on 7/29. 1/2" rain last night.
Overcast at Saturday flyover this morning.
Very calm- very humid. showers yesterday. 0.13" rain.
2 inches of rain in past week. Lake level still low.
Temps in 30's first time this fall- this morning.
Have had light frost. some flowers still thriving.
Some very heavy rains in past week.  Loon still here two days ago.
Little green heron seen daily.  Big blue heron not as often.
Maximum temperatures have been 10 degrees F below normal past week with 1.3" of rain.
1.5" of rain since last sample.  Maximum temperatures have still been 70 degrees F- below normal- warming up today.

No rain and the temperature has been at 90 degrees F for the last five days.
Only traces of rain in the past few weeks.  Near record low temperature four days ago.

2+" of rain in the past ten days.  The weather is hot and humid.
Temperature in the 80's today after nine days in the 90's.
2.5" of rain in the past week.
3.5" of rain in the past five days.

Surface water temp 83.5 F- sunny- wind 160 degrees @5-8 kt

Hazy clear sky.  Wind 160 degrees @5 kt.  DAK assist.
Air temp 33 degrees.  Wind 110 degrees @ 8-10 kt.  High thin overcast
P. Sunny.  wind calm.  Surface water temp 63 degrees.  Some clump black and green algae starting.

column1: Moderate pine pollen and clump algae both earlier and worse than prior couple years at similar dates.  Mayflies waning- extremely light year.

column2: Water temp 76 degrees- wind 160 degrees @10 kt- sunny.  Pine pollen nearly over with increased water clarity from prior week

Worst outcropping of algae ever observed.  90% of lake surface coverage at density of ~2 clumps/sq ft.  North shoreline with aggregated solid algae 0 to 3-6 feet from shoreline.  Routine distance swimming not possible due to algae.  Underwater plants especially on South and SE side of lake in shallow water coated with thick layer of algae.

Water 76 Degrees.  Wind 170 degrees at 8 kt.  Floating clump algae is reduced from prior week's worst case- with ~70% lake surface coverage (having 1 clump per 0.75 sq ft)- mostly depths 0-6 inch depth.

column1: Water chemistry (phosphorus and chlorophyll) samples taken today and driven to Madison for analysis

column2: Wind 150 degrees @ 3 kt.  Mostly sunny.  Algae on shoreline subsided significantly.  Algae with density of ~1 clump per 4 sq ft- covering ~60% of lake surface has diminished from prior report.
sunny- wind 180 degrees @ 5 kt.  Algae clumps reduced further from prior week- and water clarity higher than prior week.

wind 50 degrees  @ 6 kt.  Mostly sunny.  Water clarity continues to improve from July 4 weekend problems- and last reading.  Small clump algae- but only infrequent and  less than 5% lake surface coverage.
Wind calm.  Mostly sunny.  2 inches of rain the day prior.  Some algae has returned- but water clarity quite clear and water temp. is higher (83 F)
Wind 260 at 6kt.  Mostly sunny.  Most surface lake algae gone.
Wind 180 degrees @ 7 kt.  Water chemistry sample taken today and driven to Madison for analysis.  Unusual observance - 1/8 dia. algae from surface to 1-2 ft depth in entire lake.  1 per 4 sq inches.

column1: Water outflow on SSE side of lake has remained flowing the entire summer

column2: Sunny- 69 F.  wind 070 degrees @ 7-10 kt.  Some pine pollen on S side of lake- just beginning it appears.  Some floating algae- but not bad.  1 loon spotted- no geese present.  Water ~2" higher than this time last year
Air 78F- M. Sunny.  Wind 120 degrees @ 2-4 kt.  Only sporadic floating algae
Partly sunny- wind 070 degrees 3-5 kt.  Air 71.  2" rain in past week.
Winds LV- Party cloudy- temp 61 degrees
Wind 120 degrees- 3-5 kt.  Party cloudy.  Some surface algea clumps and small amount of black algea.  Light pine pollen on water surface
